Longitudinal Section of 
   Piper aduncum root inoculated with mycorrhizal fungi arbuscular (AMFs). 
   a Control sample; 
   b Penetration of hyphae in epidermal cells with formation of hyphopodium in 30 dpi; 
   c Intense colonization in 60 dpi; 
   d Colonization in 90 dpi; 
   e Formation of vesicles in 90 dpi; 
   f Hyphae inter- and intracellularly and formation of arbuscules in 90 dpi; 
   g Hepatic anastomosis in 90 dpi; (Filled circle) Hyphopodium; (Filled square) Intracellular hyphae; ( 
    ) Vesicles; (★) Arbuscules; (Filled triangle) Arbuscular trunks; ( 
    ) Hyphatic anastomosis
